<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1914-05-05T19:00:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1914-05-05T19:00:00-05:00" n="1615" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d1615">
                            <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 312.93/76.</note>
                            <head>
                                <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of State</gloss>
                                    to Consul <persName type="to">Letcher</persName>.</hi>
                            </head>
                            <opener>
                                <seg rendition="#center">[Telegram.]</seg>
                            </opener>
                            <opener>
                                <dateline rendition="#right">
                                    <placeName>
                                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Department of State</hi>, <lb/>
                                        <hi rend="italic">Washington</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1914-05-05T19:00:00-05:00">
                                        <hi rend="italic">May 5, 1914, 7 p.m.</hi>
                                    </date>
                                </dateline>
                            </opener>
                            <p>Secretary of Labor states that newspaper reports of intention to
                                modify regulations for admission of Chinese without foundation, but
                                that “Whenever it becomes necessary in the interest of humanity and
                                to save the lives of refugees to give them temporary asylum that
                                course is being followed.”</p>
                            <closer>
                                <signed>
                                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Bryan</hi></signed>.</closer>
                        </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>